Explain the entire java life cycle.
There are three main stages in the life cycle of a java program. They are:
Editing the program--The program is written in in a text-editor and saved as with the extension as(.java)Compiling the source code--The compilation input to the compiler is Java source code which is in Sample.java and the comelier will generate the bytecode file as Sample.class.
Executing the byte code--The bytecode generated by the compiler is executed by Java Virtual Machine (JVM).
JVM is has the following components---1.Class Loader will load the bytecode in JVM
 2.Bytecode Verifier will verify the sample.class
 3.Execution Engine will execute code and generate the code that is readable by computer.
