Why main is static?
The main method is always called by JVM to start the execution of code without object.Hnece it is always static as it is nowhere related to any object.
It is a keyword in java which identifies it is class based i.e it can be accessed without creating the instance of a Class.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What is the difference between an Interface and Abstract class?
Abstract class can have abstract and complete methods where are the interface has only abstract methods.
Abstract class doesn't support multiple inheritance. wheresa the interface supports the multiple inheritance.
Abstract class can have final, non-final, static and non-static variables where as the interface has only static and final variables.
The abstract keyword is used to declare abstract class where as The interface keyword is used to declare interface.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Can you make an Object from an Interface and Abstract class ? if not how do you use it ?
yes. it is possible to make an Object from an Interface and Abstract class.
we can extend / implement the Abstract class / interface in a new class, create the object of this new class and then use this object as per to call the abstract class /interface.
