What is OOP ? Define each feature of java OOP.
	Object Oriented Programming language/system.
	1. Encapsulation--Encapsulation  means binding object state and behaviour(methods) together.
	2. Abstraction--Abstraction is a process of hiding the implementation details and showing only  “relevant” data of an object from the user.
	3. Polymorphism--it is the mechanism to perform a single action in different ways.
	4. Inheritance--The process by which one class acquires the properties(data members) and functionalities(methods) of another class is called inheritance.

