What is method overloading and when it happens?
when methods of the class share teh same name but with different parameters and different sequnce of parameters and data types.
It happens at compile time Polymorphism.

Explain exceptions in java and how to handle it.
An exception is an event, which occurs during the execution of a program, that disrupts the normal flow of the program's instructions.
The throws keyword appears at the end of a method's signature. We can throw an exception by using the throw keyword.

What is static keyword in java? How it has been used in variables and methods ?
static keyword is used in Java and it is applied to a method,inner class or to a field.If a variable is declared as static variable then
this variables can not be used can be accessed directly by the class name and doesn't need any object. If one object changes a static variable value, it changes for all other objects.
Static method is a method which belongs to the class and not to the object. It can be accessed directly by the class name and doesn't need any object.


What is final and how it has been used variables and methods?
final is the reserved keyword in Java.It is the modifier which is applicable to the classes,methods and variables.
if variables are declared as final then they become as constant and the re-assignment value of those variables is not possible.If method is defined as "final"then that method can not be override.

What is final, finally and finalize?
final--is the modifier in Java which is applicable only to class,methods and variables such as if class is declared as final then the derived classes are not possible.
finally--it is a block which is always associted with try catch.Clean up codes activities are maintained in finally block after the try catch block.
finalize--is a method that is called by garbage collector to clean up the objects if they are no more in use.

What is a constructor ?
It is the instance of class which is used to initialize the objects of the class.
It must have the same name as that of the class.it has no return type and it is automatically called when an object is created.
There are two types of constructors:Default constructor & Parameterized constructor.

What is "this" keyword in java ?
It is used to represents the instance of a class in which they appear.It is also used to access class memebers and reference to the currebt instance.

What is "super" keyword in java?
This Keyword is used to access the members of the class inherited by the class in which they appear.It also allows a subclass to access the overrideen methods of the superclass.

